            "body": "\"Maybe\" defines a class attribute (i.e. a single value shared between all instances, rather than one value per instance) - It's allowed but it doesn't do what you think. It's mostly consistent with what would happen if you put `a=0` in an ordinary class definition (the self.a assignment doesn't work though, understandably). It's unlikely to be the source of your bug.",
